I was doubting whether this should use the code from `ScalaErrorReporter` instead, like this:

```scala
  private def scalacAnalyze(doc: m.Document): Seq[Diagnostic] = {
    val index = EagerInMemorySemanticdbIndex(
      m.Database(doc :: Nil),
      m.Sourcepath(Nil),
      m.Classpath(Nil)
    )
    for {
      doc <- index.database.documents
      msg <- doc.messages
    } yield msg.toLSP("scalac")
  }
```

I tried it, but it was glitchy so I left it as is. I don't understand very well why `EagerInMemorySemanticdbIndex` was used there and whether it should be used here. Semanticdbs we get here are already built interactively, isn't it enough?
